            <h1>Zone API Documentation</h1>
            <p>Welcome to the Zone API documentation. This guide provides everything you need to integrate Zone's
                AI-driven capabilities into your existing systems and applications. Our API is designed to be RESTful,
                easy to use, and highly efficient.</p>

            <h2>Getting Started</h2>
            <h3>Authentication</h3>
            <p>All requests to the Zone API require API-key authentication. This ensures secure access to our services.
                Follow these steps to authenticate:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Obtain API Key: Register on our platform to receive your unique API key.</li>
                <li>Include in Request Header: Use the API key in the header of every API request.</li>
            </ol>

            <h3>Backend Modules</h3>
            <p>Our API offers a range of backend modules including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Chat Interface Integration: Seamlessly integrate real-time chat functionalities.</li>
                <li>SOP Query Processing: Leverage our AI to process complex SOP queries efficiently.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Endpoints</h3>
            <p>The Zone API provides various endpoints to access different functionalities:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>/query: Submit and retrieve responses to SOP-related queries.</li>
                <li>/authenticate: Manage your API key and session.</li>
                <li>/error: Handle and understand error responses.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Rate Limits</h3>
            <p>To maintain service quality and prevent abuse, our API implements rate limits. Detailed information about
                these limits will be provided in your API key package.</p>

            <h3>Error Handling</h3>
            <p>We use standard HTTP response codes to indicate the success or failure of an API request. Examples
                include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>200 OK: Successful request.</li>
                <li>401 Unauthorized: Authentication error.</li>
                <li>500 Internal Server Error: General server error.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Hosting and Scalability</h3>
            <p>Hosted on AWS Elastic, our API guarantees high availability and scalability to meet varying demands.</p>
